title: On the Rebound
description: An old flame returns to pick up where she left off with Mark - until Vanessa and Robin learn her real intentions.

title: How to Succeed in Business Without Really Trying
Baby Love
description: Mark has to make a tough decision when his cousins Geneva and Nichole pay a visit.

title: Slumber Party
description: Mark becomes a not-so-willing host of a birthday party for Nichole after Geneva and Vanessa experience car trouble.

title: Father Fairest
description: Earvin and his father are reunited by Mark. A school carnival is thrown.

title: The Goodbye Girl
description: Nicole wants a "divorce" from Geneva.

title: Seoul Shake
description: Dante Basco guest stars as a Korean-American student who wishes to join Mark's basketball team.

title: Prince of Soul
description: Guest star Don Cheadle plays an reputed African prince whom Vanessa plans to marry. Mark offers his opinions.

title: Santa's Got a Brand New Bag

Hero
description: The truth about Mark's heroics comes out when the mayor presents him with an award.

title: Here Comes the Groom
description: Earvin misunderstands Mark's advice and decides to elope.

title: The Matchmaker
description: During a surprise visit, superstitious Aunt Eunetta reads the heads of Mark and Vanessa and decides that they share a future. Mark and Vanessa, who eventually would be engaged, share a kiss to dispel her prediction and discover that they enjoy kissing each other.

title: Guys' Night Out
description: Geneva's dull boyfriend tags along on Mark's birthday celebration; Nicole hides a kitten.

title: A Matter of Principal
description: Mark things he can do whatever he wants not the Geneva is the new principal of the high school.

title: The Great Pretender
description: Mark pretends to be wounded to gain the attention and sympathy of an attractive neighbor. Also, Nichole wants to dress herself and to stop getting advise from Geneva.

title: Increase the Peace
description: Mark intervenes when a gun-toting gang member threatens Earvin at school threatens Earvin at school.

title: Coach Counselor
description: Mark's first challenge as a guidance counselor is a basketball player who has an inflated ego.

title: Breaking Up Is Hard to Do
description: Mark and Vanessa discover their feelings for each other run very deep after they try to break up.

title: Will She or Won't She?
description: Mark plans a romantic way to proposing marriage to Vanessa.

title: The In-Laws
description: Mark attempts to make a favorable impression on the parents of Vanessa in order to get them to pay the wedding expenses, but he ends up embarrassing himself.

roles.char: Man Outside Oakland City Ballet Company

title: The Swami
description: To help the school earn money for textbooks, Mark works at a carnival pretending to be a fortuneteller. To help Geneva secure a donation from baby food millionaire Mr Rosen, Mark pretends to be a real swami.

title: Getting Personal
description: After Mark refuses to take their upcoming nuptials seriously, Vanessa tries a new approach to grab his attention.
